in cystic fibrosis had remained unknown. In 1983 Quinton and Bijman TM first observed that the electrical potential of the sweat ductal lumen is about twice as negative in cystic fibrosis ducts ( - 6 0 mV) as in normal ducts ( - 3 0 mV) both in vivo and in vitro. ~~13~It also was observed that the lumen of the normal duct, but not of the cystic


